      <num>SEC. 2.67</num>
      <heading>Members—Rights, privileges, immunities, etc</heading>
      <content>
        <p>In all matters pertaining to the enforcement of the police regulations of the city
               each police officer of the city shall have and enjoy all the rights, privileges, immunities
               and protection that are now, or may be hereafter, conferred by law on peace officers
               of the state.</p>
        <p>(Code 1938, Sec. 193; Ord. No. 15.79, 4/9/79.)</p>
      </content>
